snippet: Officials looking into the personal records of Lt. Col. Jeffrey Krusinski, who ran the Air Force’s sexual assault prevention and response branch, have found no sign of trouble.
abstract: Air Force officials say Lt Col Jeffrey Krusinski, officer who ran its sexual assault prevention programs, had clean record before his arrest on sexual battery charge.
lead_paragraph: Officials looking into the personal records of Lt. Col. Jeffrey Krusinski, who ran the Air Force’s sexual assault prevention and response branch, have found no sign of trouble.

headline.main: Officer Had Clean Record, Air Force Says
